You can use [rxdart](https://pub.dev/packages/rxdart) package for that:

```dart
Stream query1 = Stream.fromIterable([1,2,3]);
Stream query2 = Stream.fromIterable([4,5,6]);

// Will emit all items in query1, then all items in query2.
Stream mergedQueries = Observable.concat([query1, query2]);

// Will emit all items in query1 or query2, whichever item comes first.
Stream mergedQueries = Observable.merge([query1, query2]);
```

Which operator to select depends on whether you want to preserve strict order. But in case of using `concat` `query1` will have to terminate prior to `query2` be able to emit items. So for the case with (probably) endless query subscriptions I think you should go with `merge` operator – when either of `query1` or `query2` streams emits items, it will be emitted by `mergedQueries`.

